Bug 2052168 - Don't open attachments on modified Enter keypress. r=babolivier

When the attachment list has focus, Ctrl+Enter (Linux/Windows) or
Cmd+Return (macOS) should send the message, not open the selected
attachment. Bug 2010213 replaced the `command` event listener with a
`keydown` handler that only checked for the Enter key without
accounting for modifier keys, and left behind the now-dead `keypress`
handler that previously dispatched the `command` event. Remove the
dead `keypress` Enter case and add modifier key checks to the `keydown`
handler so only a plain, unmodified Enter opens attachments.

Added tests for opening attachments with the Enter key and for
ensuring modified Enter (Cmd+Return on macOS, Ctrl+Enter elsewhere)
does not trigger attachment open.

Also fixes bug 1905613.

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310513


